{"author":{"id":"b0444bc5323d62d0119f1b38989b02f86da411aca9444e686fe63246c2266998"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1668589006,"nonce":"mWoC1ANvDVHXC5A4LyjlrtaoAXk=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5WfwoF","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4930","origin":"github"},"title":"PyEGA3 recognizes collections of vcf_bgzip files as vcf","message":"When downloading vcf.gz files from the EGA using the PyEGA3 tool using the `Download multiple files` option it recognizes the files as vcfs. However, when downloading the files they are still gzipped vcf files. This causes an error when using the collection for tools like `bcftools`. It first tries to compress the bgzip file, because it recognizes it as a vcf, see command:\n```\nexport BCFTOOLS_PLUGINS=`which bcftools | sed 's,bin/bcftools,libexec/bcftools,'`;     bgzip -c '/data/dnb07/galaxy_db/files/1/f/7/dataset_1f753c41-0de8-45f7-b54b-1fd112a436d2.dat' \u003e input0.vcf.gz \u0026\u0026 bcftools index input0.vcf.gz \u0026\u0026 echo 'input0.vcf.gz' \u003e\u003e vcfs_list \u0026\u0026  bgzip -c '/data/dnb06/galaxy_db/files/7/d/9/dataset_7d9afefc-28f8-469a-be32-556d1ec506c5.dat' \u003e input1.vcf.gz \u0026\u0026 bcftools index input1.vcf.gz \u0026\u0026 echo 'input1.vcf.gz' \u003e\u003e vcfs_list \u0026\u0026  bgzip -c '/data/dnb06/galaxy_db/files/0/9/8/dataset_09870417-f38e-49f9-a050-979ad41ccecd.dat' \u003e input2.vcf.gz \u0026\u0026 bcftools index input2.vcf.gz \u0026\u0026 echo 'input2.vcf.gz' \u003e\u003e vcfs_list \u0026\u0026         bcftools merge                 --output-type 'v'   --threads ${GALAXY_SLOTS:-4}    input0.vcf.gz input1.vcf.gz input2.vcf.gz  \u003e '/data/jwd01/main/052/282/52282722/outputs/galaxy_dataset_218112e7-a286-40fa-b2ea-82d4e7e46c85.dat'\n```\nand returns:\n```\n[E::hts_hopen] Failed to open file input0.vcf.gz\n[E::hts_open_format] Failed to open file \"input0.vcf.gz\" : Exec format error\nindex: failed to open \"input0.vcf.gz\"\n```\n\nBefore the files were recognized as `gz` files, so that was also causing issues. Here is the PR to fix it #4841 \nI tried to fix this by adding the `vcf_bgzip` extension to all vcf.gz files, so it becomes `vcf.gz.vcf_bgzip` maybe this messes up the automatic recognition of the files, since there are two extensions? I'm thinking of fixing this by replacing the `vcf.gz` with `vcf_bgzip` or do you think the issue is caused by something else? I would like to hear your thoughts on this.","files":null}]}